<p><br />
The metric system was adopted in France on December 10, 1799 by which time Pascal's basic design had inspired other craftsmen, although with a similar lack of commercial success.</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Known_machines">Known machines</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Pascal%27s_calculator&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Known machines">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Most of the machines that have survived the centuries are of the accounting type. Seven of them are in European museums, one belongs to the IBM corporation and one is in private hands.</p>
